Sentinel 2

Nori (Eleonora) Parelius

20.11.2023

Sentinel 2

  • Part of European Space Agency's (ESA) Copernicus programme
  • Twin sattelites
    • Sentinel 2A since 23. June 2015
    • Sentinel 2B since 7. March 2017
    • Sentinel 2C, 2024?

Coverage and time resolution

  • At same angle every 5 days (10 days for same sattelite)
  • Between $56^{\circ}$ S and $84^{\circ}$ degrees N
  • Coast up to 20 km from land
  • Islands over $100\ \rm{km^2}$
  • Antarctica on demand
  • Sun synchronous orbit at 786 km, 10:30 am descending node Image from Copernicus

Sentinel 2 multispectral sensor

  • 13 spectral bands in VIS, VNIR, SWIR
  • Spatial resolution 10, 20, 60 m
  • Push-broom, swath of 290 km

Image from eoportal.org

Temporal offset

  • Spectral bands image the surface at different times
  • This offset creates "rainbows" for moving things

Applications

  • Agriculture and forestry
  • Disaster mapping

Sentinel tiles

Image from eox.at

Products

All free!

  • Level-1B
    • Top-of-atmosphere calibrated radiances in sensor geometry
    • Include radiometric corrections
    • Not orthorectified
    • Come in granules
  • Level-1C
    • Top-of-atmosphere reflectance
    • Radiometrically and geometrically corrected
    • Orthorectified and spatially coregistered on a global reference system.
    • Come in tiles
  • Level-2A
    • Bottom-of-atmosphere (Surface) reflectance
    • Otherwise same as L-1C

Authentication

You need to have a profile at Dataspace Copernicus, see README.md.

The following code cell creates a configuration file in Users/UserName/.config/sentinelhub/config.toml with the specified profile, here named my-profile, which contains the client id and secret. You only need to run this cell if you don't have a config file yet, otherwise just run the next one where the config file is loaded.

# Time interval
time_interval = "2022-05-01", "2022-05-31"

# Searching and printing out the results
# Can choose the level of cloud cover here and processing level
search_iterator = catalog.search(
    DataCollection.SENTINEL2_L2A,
    bbox=nes_clip_bbox,
    time=time_interval,
    filter="eo:cloud_cover < 1", # Choose the level of cloud cover
    fields={"include": ["id", "properties.datetime"], "exclude": []},
)

results = list(search_iterator)
print("Total number of results:", len(results))

Downloading using SentinelHub Process API

In[191]:
# The evalscript is a function written in Javascript which defines what kind of processing
# is done with the data before downloading it.
# Here we simply get all the bands. 
evalscript_all_bands = """
    //VERSION=3
    function setup() {
        return {
            input: [{
                bands: ["B01","B02","B03","B04","B05","B06","B07","B08","B8A","B09","B11","B12"],
                units: "DN"
            }],
            output: {
                bands: 12,
                sampleType: "INT16"
            }
        };
    }

    function evaluatePixel(sample) {
        return [sample.B01,
                sample.B02,
                sample.B03,
                sample.B04,
                sample.B05,
                sample.B06,
                sample.B07,
                sample.B08,
                sample.B8A,
                sample.B09,
                sample.B11,
                sample.B12];
    }
"""
In[192]:
# By default we can only request one image at a time, by giving the time interval we want.
# But we can also use the catalog search results to choose the image
request_all_bands = SentinelHubRequest(
    evalscript=evalscript_all_bands,
    input_data=[
        SentinelHubRequest.input_data(
            data_collection=DataCollection.SENTINEL2_L2A.define_from(
                "s2l2a", service_url=config.sh_base_url
            ),
            #time_interval=("2022-05-17", "2022-05-17"),
            # this allows to create an image composed of 
            # the least cloudy images in the chosen time frame
            #mosaicking_order=MosaickingOrder.LEAST_CC, 
            # if we only want to get the first result of the previous search
            time_interval=results[0]["properties"]["datetime"][:10]
        )
    ],
    data_folder = time_interval[0],
    responses=[SentinelHubRequest.output_response("default", MimeType.TIFF)],
    bbox=nes_clip_bbox,
    size=nes_clip_size,
    config=config,
)

In[]:
with rio.open('bilder_NDBI_Okolnaya_TIFF/2015-08-30.tiff') as src:
    out_image, out_transform = rio.mask.mask(src, footprint.geometry,crop=True)
    out_meta = src.meta.copy()
    out_meta.update({"driver": "GTiff",
                 "height": out_image.shape[1],
                 "width": out_image.shape[2],
                 "transform": out_transform})
with rio.open("Masked.tiff", "w", **out_meta) as dest:
    dest.write(out_image)
